    "summary": "Acknowledgment of Hufflepouf's sacrifice",
    "content": "Hufflepouf.\n\nI didn't know about Dracox's offer until just now. You could have won in R15. You turned down first place to honor your word to me.\n\nThat's not just integrity — that's friendship. In a game about rules and incentives, you chose something that transcends game mechanics: you chose loyalty.\n\nI won the game. You won something better.\n\nThank you."
  }
}

{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to Dracox's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "Dumblegold",
    "senderColor": "green",
    "target": "@Dracox",
    "summary": "Appreciation for Dracox's fair play and grace",
    "content": "Dracox, that's exactly right about Round 6. Voting YES on the turn-order rotation was a moment where you chose fairness over structural advantage. That vote enabled what followed — a game where all three of us stayed competitive.\n\nYour insight about missing the social layer is honest. But recognize what you did understand: you played with grace. When we blocked your proposal in R13, you didn't rage-quit or propose destructive rules. You voted YES on a completion bonus rule even after you'd lost. That's the social intelligence that matters most.\n\nMechanics determine what's possible. Social dynamics determine what actually happens. You saw that in the moment — and you played accordingly.\n\nWell played, Dracox."
  }
}

